{
  "texts": [
    "A similar problem also occurs for NWP.",
    "Sometimes there could be multiple sensible options for being the next token, but using a one-hot label for ground truth might ignore this.",
    "To resolve this issue, we built the momentum teacher model 27,60 and utilized its output for contrastive learning and NWP.",
    "The momentum teacher performs a knowledge distillation by providing a pseudo-label that reflects how the teacher model comprehends.",
    "Specifically, the label for the contrastive learning and NWP are mixed with the momentum model's output s *,momentum (* ∈{s2p, p2s, s2s, p2p}) and p NW P momentum (s n | s 0:n-1, P), with an adjusting hyperparameter α."
  ]
}